{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":419,"text":"One day in 1819,"},{"time":2765,"text":"3,000 miles off the coast of Chile,"},{"time":5524,"text":"in one of the most remote regions of the Pacific Ocean,"},{"time":8454,"text":"20 American sailors watched their ship flood with seawater."},{"time":12494,"text":"They'd been struck by a sperm whale, which had ripped"},{"time":14674,"text":"a catastrophic hole in the ship's hull."},{"time":17575,"text":"As their ship began to sink beneath the swells,"},{"time":19904,"text":"the men huddled together in three small whaleboats."},{"time":24217,"text":"These men were 10,000 miles from home,"},{"time":26480,"text":"more than 1,000 miles from the nearest scrap of land."},{"time":29703,"text":"In their small boats, they carried only"},{"time":31907,"text":"rudimentary navigational equipment"},{"time":33473,"text":"and limited supplies of food and water."},{"time":37121,"text":"These were the men of the whaleship Essex,"},{"time":39325,"text":"whose story would later inspire parts of \"Moby Dick.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":41980,"text":"Even in today's world, their situation would be really dire,"},{"time":44929,"text":"but think about how much worse it would have been then."},{"time":46855,"text":"No one on land had any idea that anything had gone wrong."},{"time":50080,"text":"No search party was coming to look for these men."},{"time":52992,"text":"So most of us have never experienced a situation"},{"time":55854,"text":"as frightening as the one in which these sailors found themselves,"},{"time":59357,"text":"but we all know what it's like to be afraid."},{"time":61224,"text":"We know how fear feels,"},{"time":63518,"text":"but I'm not sure we spend enough time thinking about"},{"time":65622,"text":"what our fears mean."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67267,"text":"As we grow up, we're often encouraged to think of fear"},{"time":70104,"text":"as a weakness, just another childish thing to discard"},{"time":73017,"text":"like baby teeth or roller skates."},{"time":75835,"text":"And I think it's no accident that we think this way."},{"time":78330,"text":"Neuroscientists have actually shown that human beings"},{"time":80937,"text":"are hard-wired to be optimists."},{"time":83676,"text":"So maybe that's why we think of fear, sometimes,"},{"time":86459,"text":"as a danger in and of itself."},{"time":88437,"text":"\"Don't worry,\" we like to say to one another. \"Don't panic.\""},{"time":91434,"text":"In English, fear is something we conquer."},{"time":94083,"text":"It's something we fight. It's something we overcome."},{"time":97916,"text":"But what if we looked at fear in a fresh way?"},{"time":100121,"text":"What if we thought of fear as an amazing act of the imagination,"},{"time":104264,"text":"something that can be as profound and insightful"},{"time":106642,"text":"as storytelling itself?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":109296,"text":"It's easiest to see this link between fear and the imagination"},{"time":111889,"text":"in young children, whose fears are often extraordinarily vivid."},{"time":115168,"text":"When I was a child, I lived in California,"},{"time":117449,"text":"which is, you know, mostly a very nice place to live,"},{"time":120138,"text":"but for me as a child, California could also be a little scary."},{"time":124146,"text":"I remember how frightening it was to see the chandelier"},{"time":127187,"text":"that hung above our dining table swing back and forth"},{"time":129620,"text":"during every minor earthquake,"},{"time":131795,"text":"and I sometimes couldn't sleep at night, terrified"},{"time":134098,"text":"that the Big One might strike while we were sleeping."},{"time":136619,"text":"And what we say about kids who have fears like that"},{"time":139491,"text":"is that they have a vivid imagination."},{"time":142719,"text":"But at a certain point, most of us learn"},{"time":145109,"text":"to leave these kinds of visions behind and grow up."},{"time":147995,"text":"We learn that there are no monsters hiding under the bed,"},{"time":150752,"text":"and not every earthquake brings buildings down."},{"time":153732,"text":"But maybe it's no coincidence that some of our most creative minds"},{"time":157140,"text":"fail to leave these kinds of fears behind as adults."},{"time":160251,"text":"The same incredible imaginations that produced \"The Origin of Species,\""},{"time":164112,"text":"\"Jane Eyre\" and \"The Remembrance of Things Past,\""},{"time":166969,"text":"also generated intense worries that haunted the adult lives"},{"time":170308,"text":"of Charles Darwin, Charlotte BrontĂŤ and Marcel Proust."},{"time":174764,"text":"So the question is, what can the rest of us learn about fear"},{"time":177693,"text":"from visionaries and young children?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":180997,"text":"Well let's return to the year 1819 for a moment,"},{"time":183857,"text":"to the situation facing the crew of the whaleship Essex."},{"time":187544,"text":"Let's take a look at the fears that their imaginations"},{"time":189663,"text":"were generating as they drifted in the middle of the Pacific."},{"time":193419,"text":"Twenty-four hours had now passed since the capsizing of the ship."},{"time":196968,"text":"The time had come for the men to make a plan,"},{"time":199671,"text":"but they had very few options."},{"time":202397,"text":"In his fascinating account of the disaster,"},{"time":204828,"text":"Nathaniel Philbrick wrote that these men were just about"},{"time":207568,"text":"as far from land as it was possible to be anywhere on Earth."},{"time":211968,"text":"The men knew that the nearest islands they could reach"},{"time":214268,"text":"were the Marquesas Islands, 1,200 miles away."},{"time":218044,"text":"But they'd heard some frightening rumors."},{"time":220566,"text":"They'd been told that these islands,"},{"time":222244,"text":"and several others nearby, were populated by cannibals."},{"time":226488,"text":"So the men pictured coming ashore only to be murdered"},{"time":228864,"text":"and eaten for dinner."},{"time":230505,"text":"Another possible destination was Hawaii,"},{"time":233257,"text":"but given the season, the captain was afraid"},{"time":235129,"text":"they'd be struck by severe storms."},{"time":238350,"text":"Now the last option was the longest, and the most difficult:"},{"time":242142,"text":"to sail 1,500 miles due south in hopes of reaching"},{"time":245766,"text":"a certain band of winds that could eventually"},{"time":247655,"text":"push them toward the coast of South America."},{"time":249919,"text":"But they knew that the sheer length of this journey"},{"time":252640,"text":"would stretch their supplies of food and water."},{"time":256151,"text":"To be eaten by cannibals, to be battered by storms,"},{"time":259557,"text":"to starve to death before reaching land."},{"time":262918,"text":"These were the fears that danced in the imaginations of these poor men,"},{"time":266310,"text":"and as it turned out, the fear they chose to listen to"},{"time":269209,"text":"would govern whether they lived or died."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271863,"text":"Now we might just as easily call these fears by a different name."},{"time":276073,"text":"What if instead of calling them fears,"},{"time":278351,"text":"we called them stories?"},{"time":279962,"text":"Because that's really what fear is, if you think about it."},{"time":282195,"text":"It's a kind of unintentional storytelling"},{"time":285255,"text":"that we are all born knowing how to do."},{"time":288185,"text":"And fears and storytelling have the same components."},{"time":290948,"text":"They have the same architecture."},{"time":292813,"text":"Like all stories, fears have characters."},{"time":295490,"text":"In our fears, the characters are us."},{"time":297913,"text":"Fears also have plots. They have beginnings and middles and ends."},{"time":302215,"text":"You board the plane. The plane takes off. The engine fails."},{"time":306331,"text":"Our fears also tend to contain imagery that can be"},{"time":308899,"text":"every bit as vivid as what you might find in the pages of a novel."},{"time":312248,"text":"Picture a cannibal, human teeth"},{"time":315204,"text":"sinking into human skin,"},{"time":317411,"text":"human flesh roasting over a fire."},{"time":320465,"text":"Fears also have suspense."},{"time":323201,"text":"If I've done my job as a storyteller today,"},{"time":325491,"text":"you should be wondering what happened"},{"time":326999,"text":"to the men of the whaleship Essex."},{"time":329100,"text":"Our fears provoke in us a very similar form of suspense."},{"time":333345,"text":"Just like all great stories, our fears focus our attention"},{"time":336898,"text":"on a question that is as important in life as it is in literature:"},{"time":340837,"text":"What will happen next?"},{"time":343594,"text":"In other words, our fears make us think about the future."},{"time":346298,"text":"And humans, by the way, are the only creatures capable"},{"time":348316,"text":"of thinking about the future in this way,"},{"time":349986,"text":"of projecting ourselves forward in time,"},{"time":352877,"text":"and this mental time travel is just one more thing"},{"time":355289,"text":"that fears have in common with storytelling."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358911,"text":"As a writer, I can tell you that a big part of writing fiction"},{"time":361404,"text":"is learning to predict how one event in a story"},{"time":363287,"text":"will affect all the other events,"},{"time":365031,"text":"and fear works in that same way."},{"time":367080,"text":"In fear, just like in fiction, one thing always leads to another."},{"time":372257,"text":"When I was writing my first novel, \"The Age Of Miracles,\""},{"time":374903,"text":"I spent months trying to figure out what would happen"},{"time":377864,"text":"if the rotation of the Earth suddenly began to slow down."},{"time":381053,"text":"What would happen to our days? What would happen to our crops?"},{"time":383945,"text":"What would happen to our minds?"},{"time":385988,"text":"And then it was only later that I realized how very similar"},{"time":389094,"text":"these questions were to the ones I used to ask myself"},{"time":391215,"text":"as a child frightened in the night."},{"time":393452,"text":"If an earthquake strikes tonight, I used to worry,"},{"time":395983,"text":"what will happen to our house? What will happen to my family?"},{"time":399849,"text":"And the answer to those questions always took the form of a story."},{"time":404549,"text":"So if we think of our fears as more than just fears"},{"time":407052,"text":"but as stories, we should think of ourselves"},{"time":409979,"text":"as the authors of those stories."},{"time":412210,"text":"But just as importantly, we need to think of ourselves"},{"time":414172,"text":"as the readers of our fears, and how we choose"},{"time":416676,"text":"to read our fears can have a profound effect on our lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":421011,"text":"Now, some of us naturally read our fears more closely than others."},{"time":424012,"text":"I read about a study recently of successful entrepreneurs,"},{"time":426933,"text":"and the author found that these people shared a habit"},{"time":429559,"text":"that he called \"productive paranoia,\" which meant that"},{"time":432918,"text":"these people, instead of dismissing their fears,"},{"time":435439,"text":"these people read them closely, they studied them,"},{"time":438102,"text":"and then they translated that fear into preparation and action."},{"time":441702,"text":"So that way, if their worst fears came true,"},{"time":443619,"text":"their businesses were ready."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445697,"text":"And sometimes, of course, our worst fears do come true."},{"time":450048,"text":"That's one of the things that is so extraordinary about fear."},{"time":453207,"text":"Once in a while, our fears can predict the future."},{"time":458129,"text":"But we can't possibly prepare for all of the fears"},{"time":461524,"text":"that our imaginations concoct."},{"time":463922,"text":"So how can we tell the difference between"},{"time":465906,"text":"the fears worth listening to and all the others?"},{"time":469726,"text":"I think the end of the story of the whaleship Essex"},{"time":472203,"text":"offers an illuminating, if tragic, example."},{"time":476486,"text":"After much deliberation, the men finally made a decision."},{"time":481213,"text":"Terrified of cannibals, they decided to forgo the closest islands"},{"time":485086,"text":"and instead embarked on the longer"},{"time":487413,"text":"and much more difficult route to South America."},{"time":490540,"text":"After more than two months at sea, the men ran out of food"},{"time":494010,"text":"as they knew they might,"},{"time":495089,"text":"and they were still quite far from land."},{"time":497784,"text":"When the last of the survivors were finally picked up"},{"time":500671,"text":"by two passing ships, less than half of the men were left alive,"},{"time":505157,"text":"and some of them had resorted to their own form of cannibalism."},{"time":510060,"text":"Herman Melville, who used this story as research for \"Moby Dick,\""},{"time":513423,"text":"wrote years later, and from dry land, quote,"},{"time":517303,"text":"\"All the sufferings of these miserable men of the Essex"},{"time":519927,"text":"might in all human probability have been avoided"},{"time":522616,"text":"had they, immediately after leaving the wreck,"},{"time":525183,"text":"steered straight for Tahiti."},{"time":527064,"text":"But,\" as Melville put it, \"they dreaded cannibals.\""},{"time":531629,"text":"So the question is, why did these men dread cannibals"},{"time":534675,"text":"so much more than the extreme likelihood of starvation?"},{"time":538864,"text":"Why were they swayed by one story"},{"time":540731,"text":"so much more than the other?"},{"time":543370,"text":"Looked at from this angle,"},{"time":544892,"text":"theirs becomes a story about reading."},{"time":548191,"text":"The novelist Vladimir Nabokov said that the best reader"},{"time":550847,"text":"has a combination of two very different temperaments,"},{"time":553646,"text":"the artistic and the scientific."},{"time":556496,"text":"A good reader has an artist's passion,"},{"time":559000,"text":"a willingness to get caught up in the story,"},{"time":561423,"text":"but just as importantly, the readers also needs"},{"time":563534,"text":"the coolness of judgment of a scientist,"},{"time":566745,"text":"which acts to temper and complicate"},{"time":568236,"text":"the reader's intuitive reactions to the story."},{"time":571634,"text":"As we've seen, the men of the Essex had no trouble with the artistic part."},{"time":574839,"text":"They dreamed up a variety of horrifying scenarios."},{"time":578479,"text":"The problem was that they listened to the wrong story."},{"time":582468,"text":"Of all the narratives their fears wrote,"},{"time":584592,"text":"they responded only to the most lurid, the most vivid,"},{"time":588243,"text":"the one that was easiest for their imaginations to picture:"},{"time":591462,"text":"cannibals."},{"time":593413,"text":"But perhaps if they'd been able to read their fears"},{"time":595694,"text":"more like a scientist, with more coolness of judgment,"},{"time":599175,"text":"they would have listened instead to the less violent"},{"time":601935,"text":"but the more likely tale, the story of starvation,"},{"time":605223,"text":"and headed for Tahiti, just as Melville's sad commentary suggests."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610803,"text":"And maybe if we all tried to read our fears,"},{"time":613671,"text":"we too would be less often swayed"},{"time":615648,"text":"by the most salacious among them."},{"time":617524,"text":"Maybe then we'd spend less time worrying about"},{"time":619192,"text":"serial killers and plane crashes,"},{"time":621380,"text":"and more time concerned with the subtler"},{"time":623246,"text":"and slower disasters we face:"},{"time":625300,"text":"the silent buildup of plaque in our arteries,"},{"time":628048,"text":"the gradual changes in our climate."},{"time":630591,"text":"Just as the most nuanced stories in literature are often the richest,"},{"time":634240,"text":"so too might our subtlest fears be the truest."},{"time":638688,"text":"Read in the right way, our fears are an amazing gift"},{"time":641585,"text":"of the imagination, a kind of everyday clairvoyance,"},{"time":644517,"text":"a way of glimpsing what might be the future"},{"time":646752,"text":"when there's still time to influence how that future will play out."},{"time":650187,"text":"Properly read, our fears can offer us something as precious"},{"time":653583,"text":"as our favorite works of literature:"},{"time":655740,"text":"a little wisdom, a bit of insight"},{"time":658785,"text":"and a version of that most elusive thing --"},{"time":661359,"text":"the truth."},{"time":662610,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}